definitions.definition: The final section of a document, often involving a formulaic close (e.g. “Yours faithfully”), the date and location of writing, and information on the document's originators e.g. author, counter-signer, witnesses present, etc.
The concluding section of a liturgical preface , following the embolism .

main_definition: ( diplomacy ) The final section of a document, often involving a formulaic close (e.g. “Yours faithfully”), the date and location of writing, and information on the document's originators e.g. author, counter-signer, witnesses present, etc.
secondary_definitions: ( Roman Catholicism ) The concluding section of a liturgical preface , following the embolism .
